<item>
            <title>[LU-1209] sanity.sh subtest test_133d failed with &quot;samedir_rename_size count error&quot;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1209</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/025d7aac-6ce3-11e1-9174-5254004bbbd3&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/025d7aac-6ce3-11e1-9174-5254004bbbd3&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This subtest is reporting 14% failure over the past 100 runs, so there must be some race or unexpected result causing the failure. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_133d failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;samedir_rename_size count error&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: sanity 133d&lt;/p&gt;</description>
